8. Risks and anti-delusion guardrails

This part matters most.

Red flags

Kill or quarantine a narrative if it:
	•	makes you less falsifiable
	•	isolates you from correction
	•	increases grandiosity
	•	encourages manipulation
	•	treats vibes as proof
	•	converts every coincidence into confirmation

Required guardrails

Every hyperstition object must have:
	•	one measurable test
	•	one disconfirming condition
	•	one ethical boundary
	•	one trusted sober review pass

Your system already has the right guards:
	•	Mirror
	•	Checksum
	•	Blacksmith
	•	Hound

So use them.

